---
import { withBase } from '../../lib/url';
import Prose from '../../layouts/Prose.astro';
import QuoteList from '../../components/QuoteList.astro';
import { TECHNIQUES } from '../../lib/techniques';

const t = TECHNIQUES.find((x) => x.slug === 'essential-dignities')!;
---

<Prose
  title={t.title}
  description={t.description}
  crumbs={[{ name: 'Techniques', href: '/techniques/' }, { name: t.title }]}
  kicker="Technique"
  jsonLd={[{ '@type': 'Article', headline: t.title }]}
>
  <p>
    A figure is not equally strong everywhere. Each figure is strong in some houses and weak in
    others, following the dignities of its ruling planet. This strength of place is its essential
    dignity. It is separate from whether the figure itself is good or ill, and it shows how much
    force a finding carries.
  </p>

  <h2>Read a figure's dignity</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Find the figure's ruling planet and element in the table below.</li>
    <li>Read each house of the chart as a sign: the first house as Aries through the twelfth as Pisces.</li>
    <li>The figure is dignified when it falls in a house answering to its planet's domicile or exaltation, and debilitated in its detriment or fall.</li>
    <li>It is also stronger where the chart around it shares its element, its triplicity.</li>
    <li>Read dignity apart from goodness: a strong place makes a figure more able to act, for good or ill.</li>
  </ol>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Figure</th><th>Planet</th><th>Triplicity</th><th>Domicile</th><th>Exaltation</th><th>Detriment</th><th>Fall</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Fortuna Major</td><td>Sun</td><td>Fire</td><td>Leo</td><td>Aries</td><td>Aquarius</td><td>Libra</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Fortuna Minor</td><td>Sun</td><td>Air</td><td>Leo</td><td>Aries</td><td>Aquarius</td><td>Libra</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Via</td><td>Moon</td><td>Water</td><td>Cancer</td><td>Taurus</td><td>Capricorn</td><td>Scorpio</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Populus</td><td>Moon</td><td>Water</td><td>Cancer</td><td>Taurus</td><td>Capricorn</td><td>Scorpio</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Acquisitio</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Water</td><td>Sagittarius, Pisces</td><td>Cancer</td><td>Gemini, Virgo</td><td>Capricorn</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Laetitia</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Air</td><td>Sagittarius, Pisces</td><td>Cancer</td><td>Gemini, Virgo</td><td>Capricorn</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Puella</td><td>Venus</td><td>Air</td><td>Taurus, Libra</td><td>Pisces</td><td>Aries, Scorpio</td><td>Virgo</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Amissio</td><td>Venus</td><td>Fire</td><td>Taurus, Libra</td><td>Pisces</td><td>Aries, Scorpio</td><td>Virgo</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Conjunctio</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Air</td><td>Gemini, Virgo</td><td>Virgo</td><td>Sagittarius, Pisces</td><td>Pisces</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Albus</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Earth</td><td>Gemini, Virgo</td><td>Virgo</td><td>Sagittarius, Pisces</td><td>Pisces</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Puer</td><td>Mars</td><td>Fire</td><td>Aries, Scorpio</td><td>Capricorn</td><td>Taurus, Libra</td><td>Cancer</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Rubeus</td><td>Mars</td><td>Fire</td><td>Aries, Scorpio</td><td>Capricorn</td><td>Taurus, Libra</td><td>Cancer</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Carcer</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Earth</td><td>Capricorn, Aquarius</td><td>Libra</td><td>Cancer, Leo</td><td>Aries</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Tristitia</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Earth</td><td>Capricorn, Aquarius</td><td>Libra</td><td>Cancer, Leo</td><td>Aries</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Caput Draconis</td><td>North Node</td><td>Earth</td><td>-</td><td>Gemini</td><td>-</td><td>-</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Cauda Draconis</td><td>South Node</td><td>Water</td><td>-</td><td>Sagittarius</td><td>-</td><td>-</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    Read each house as a sign for this table: the first house answers to Aries and the twelfth to
    Pisces. The Dragon's Head and Tail keep only their exaltations.
  </p>
  <p>The figure table is built from the classical dignities of the signs:</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Sign</th><th>Ruler</th><th>Detriment</th><th>Exaltation</th><th>Fall</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Aries</td><td>Mars</td><td>Venus</td><td>Sun</td><td>Saturn</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Taurus</td><td>Venus</td><td>Mars</td><td>Moon</td><td>-</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gemini</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>North Node</td><td>-</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Cancer</td><td>Moon</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Mars</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Leo</td><td>Sun</td><td>Saturn</td><td>-</td><td>-</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Virgo</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Venus</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Libra</td><td>Venus</td><td>Mars</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Sun</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Scorpio</td><td>Mars</td><td>Venus</td><td>-</td><td>Moon</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Sagittarius</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Mercury</td><td>South Node</td><td>-</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Capricorn</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Moon</td><td>Mars</td><td>Jupiter</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Aquarius</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Sun</td><td>-</td><td>-</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Pisces</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Venus</td><td>Mercury</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>In the sources</h2>
  <QuoteList topic="dignities" noFigures />
  <p>
    Cattan's reckoning of each figure's good and ill houses, the everyday dignity tool, is quoted on
    the <a href={withBase('/figures/')}>individual figure pages</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Golden Dawn sets the same scheme out house by house in the library:
    <a href={withBase('/library/crowley/dignities-and-aspects/')}>the Table of Essential Dignities</a>.
    It is fuller on the nodes, giving Caput Draconis the dignities of Jupiter and Venus and Cauda
    Draconis those of Saturn and Mars; the table above keeps the nodes to their exaltations.
  </p>
</Prose>
